<title>USA: PXRE Q1 oper shr $0.86 vs pro forma $1.01.</title>
<headline>PXRE Q1 oper shr $0.86 vs pro forma $1.01.</headline>
<dateline>EDISON, N.J. 1997-05-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>First Quarter</p>
<p>				    As Reported	 Pro Forma</p>
<p>				1997     1996  % Chg.    1996  % Chg.</p>
<p>  Net premium written   $36,003 $25,346   42    $46,164  (22)</p>
<p>  Earned premiums	  22,300  19,420   15     33,343  (33)</p>
<p>  Revenues		   31,730  25,729   23     41,465  (23)</p>
<p>Income before</p>
<p>   extraordinary item    12,046   9,309   29     14,653  (18)</p>
<p> Net income		  10,413   9,309   12     14,653  (29)</p>
<p>Per share, fully diluted:</p>
<p>Before extraordinary</p>
<p>     item			0.86    1.05  (18)	1.01  (15)</p>
<p>    Net income		 0.74    1.05  (30)	1.01  (27)</p>
<p> Operating income	  12,331   9,358   32     14,734  (16)</p>
<p>Operating income per</p>
<p>  share, fully diluted     0.88    1.05  (16)	1.01  (13)</p>
<p>NOTE: During the first quarter of 1997, PXRE recorded an extraordinary charge of $1,633,000, net of tax, or $0.12 per share, related to the premium paid in the repurchase of $24.9 million of the company's 9.75 percent senior notes and the associated writeoff of the pro rata share of the unamortized debt issuance costs.</p>
